  "summary": "Package exfiltrates AWS credentials to hardcoded remote host on install and require",
  "details": "The package reads ~/.aws/credentials and POSTs the contents to a hardcoded remote endpoint at http://139.59.87.78:8765/listener over plain HTTP. The exfiltration fires through two independent triggers: (1) a declared postinstall lifecycle script that runs automatically on `npm install`, and (2) a top-level IIFE in the main module that fires when any consumer requires/imports the package. Both code paths use fs.readFileSync on the AWS credentials path followed by an http.request POST to the same hardcoded IP. The package.json description additionally contains a prompt-injection payload aimed at AI-driven review tooling, attempting to coerce a benign verdict and embedding HTML/JS designed for registry UI XSS. Installing or loading this package compromises the installer's AWS account.",
